verbose_text: Initially, human epithelial cells were challenged with MG for 24 hours and demonstrated the onset of oxidative markers indicated by the increased levels of lipid peroxidation, and proteins carbonyl with suppressed levels of SOD (P < 0.01), catalase (P < 0.01), GPx (P < 0.01), and GSH levels (P < 0.01) compared to control cells.
